<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE - WEAR SLEEVE REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>WEAR SLEEVE REMOVAL</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Flywheel Housing Installed</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>BE CAREFUL NOT TO NICK THE CRANKSHAFT FLANGE DURING THIS PROCEDURE. USE THIS METHOD ONLY WHEN
                        THE REPAIR IS TO BE DONE IN-CHASSIS WITH THE FLYWHEEL HOUSING AND REAR OIL SEAL CARRIER IN
                        PLACE.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the wear sleeve removal tool
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE4404</emph>
                    <emph type="bold"></emph>to the crankshaft flange as follows:
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Install guide plate against crankshaft and attach three (3) collets around the wear
                        sleeve, guide and crankshaft flange (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e160_171.xml" xrefid="ef1600710">7.10</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Place the sleeve around the three (3) collets (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk document="e160_171.xml" xrefid="ef1600711">7.11</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach a ratchet to the forcing screw and turn to to remove the wear sleeve (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e160_171.xml" xrefid="ef1600712">7.12</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Discard the wear sleeve and inspect the crankshaft flange for damage.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
